id: pm-je50
title: "Promote plan workflow primitives to the public SDK: plan create/steps/dependencies/decisions/discoveries/validation/materialization"
description: "pm plan implements durable agent planning workflows (Codex/Claude/Cursor-style: steps with status transitions, dependencies, decisions, discoveries, validation results, materialization into tracked items) but its orchestration lives CLI-side and is not covered by any existing promotion item. SDK-first plus the universal-tool story (pm-w89s) require plan primitives to be public typed API so agent harnesses, MCP pm_plan, and custom tools consume the same engine. Duplicate check: pm-v7dj (closed original plan feature), pm-z5nb (open Plan item about the schema epic, unrelated); no open SDK-promotion overlap."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 2
tags[3]: architecture,"area:plan","area:sdk"
created_at: "2026-07-05T05:09:13.638Z"
updated_at: "2026-07-11T16:06:03.401Z"
closed_at: "2026-07-11T14:11:24.830Z"
author: maintainer-agent
estimated_minutes: 240
acceptance_criteria: "SDK exports typed plan primitives covering the full pm plan surface (create with stepTitle, step lifecycle, dependencies, decisions, discoveries, validation, materialize) with identical governance and history semantics; CLI and MCP plan surfaces consume only these primitives; docstrings + linked tests + SDK reference docs; zero behavior change (plan specs green)."
parent: pm-usfg
risk: medium
confidence: medium
resolution: implemented
expected_result: pm plan create/steps/deps/decisions/discoveries/validate/materialize callable via typed PmClient without CLI shell-out
actual_result: "PmClient.plan(...) facade shipped in PR#512 with contracts, docs/SDK.md, 100% coverage; tarball consumer verified init→materialize"
